Detailed Description

cvmx_nqm_vf::_vec::_msix_int_st

NQM_VF(x)_VEC(0..16)_MSIX_INT_ST contains MSI-X vector coalescing internal state for function x. NQM_VF_MODE[VF_MODE] selects the MSI-X table entries that are actually present in the hardware. The NQM_VF_INT_VEC_E enumeration describes the table entries available in each function. See NQM_VF_INT_VEC_E and NQM_VF_MODE_E.

This CSR can be freely read. It should only ever be written in migration cases, and only ever written with zero. Refer to the migration sequence in the NQM_VF()_MSIX_PBA description.
